How do you better format your Map visualization in Power BI?

To finalize your map, you need to do the following formatting as shown below

 

Click on the Format Icon.

Click on the “Data Color” drop-down and click “Advanced Controls.”




A new screen will pop up and check off Diverging to make sure it is checked.

When the Diverging slider is on, you can set the colors for Minimum, Maximum and Center separately. In the following image, Center is set to one, so plots with values above the COUNT are a gradient shade of green, and plots below the COUNT are shades of red.



Click Okay to continue.

Your colors are now formatting.




Make sure Category and Auto Zoom are on as well.






Make sure “Title”, “Tooltip” and “Visual Header” are on as well.




Your Final views should look similar to below.




And the drill down.
